# Cursor rules — kit integration
#
# Cursor reads .cursorrules from project root. These rules tell the
# agent to lean on kit instead of inventing ad-hoc shell.
# Copy this file into your project root.

After any non-trivial edit batch, run `kit check --category security`
and surface any `fail` results before continuing. If the user asks to
install a dependency, run `kit triage <ecosystem> <package>` first.

The kit MCP server is registered at `.cursor/mcp.json`; prefer the
`kit_check`, `kit_fix`, `kit_install`, and `kit_triage`
tools over raw shell when available.

Never bypass `kit check` failures with `--no-verify` or by editing
the hook configuration without explicit user approval.
